  "decision_notes": "The problem requires logical rule chaining across a large set of rules to determine if a specific state transition occurs. I will split this into rule extraction/mapping and logical path tracing.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "rule_mapper",
      "instructions": "Analyze the 45 provided rules and create a directed graph or a structured list of causal relationships. Identify every rule that mentions the butterfly, the fish, or any intermediate entities/states that connect them. Map out all possible paths that could lead from a butterfly action to a fish action."
    },
    {
      "label": "logic_tracer",
      "instructions": "Using the structured rule map provided, attempt to trace a complete logical chain from the butterfly revealing a secret to the fish receiving it. Determine if the rules provide sufficient information to confirm the event, deny the event, or if there is a gap in the causal chain that makes the outcome impossible to determine."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the rule map and the trace results to determine if a complete, unbroken chain of rules exists that leads to the specific conclusion. If the chain is broken or information is missing, conclude that the answer is unknown."
}

